Mitch McConnell’s proposal gets it backwards and leaves working people behind. It provides:

-the least help to the people who need it most;
-tax giveaways for the biggest corporations;
-and neglects paid sick leave for workers.

We have to do better.

.@WSJ: as many as 810K COVID19 patients could need ventilators by end of May

Right now the US has only ~62K ventilators &amp; another 98k that could work in an emergency

@SecAzar: use the Defense Production Act to make sure hospitals have the equipment they need to treat patients
